    "title": {
        "rendered": "Filters Settings overview"
    },
    "content": {
        "rendered": "\n<p>Use the filter settings to change image appearance with a duotone overlay.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To apply a filter to an image, add a block containing an image \u2014 some examples are the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/image-block/\">Image Block</a> or the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/cover-block/\">Cover Block</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-background\" style=\"background-color:#e5f5fa\">Refer to this article for&nbsp;<a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/adding-a-new-block/\">detailed instructions on adding blocks</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Using filters</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>While using a block with image, you can go to the <strong>Style</strong> tab and select a filter.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"560\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/08/image-1024x560.png\" alt=\"Example of selected duotone filter\" class=\"wp-image-16358590\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/08/image-1024x560.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/08/image-300x164.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/08/image-768x420.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/08/image-1536x840.png 1536w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/08/image-2048x1120.png 2048w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The filter options provide several duotone preset to choose from. Alternatively, you can set the color for shadows and highlights yourself by clicking the color bar.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Adding to Global Styles</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>It is also possible to add filters to Global Styles \u2014 you can see more about that on the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/styles-overview/\">Styles Overview</a> page.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>When selecting a block containing an image on Global Styles, you have the option to apply a specific filter by default on all existing and new images.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"560\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/08/image-2-1024x560.png\" alt=\"Example of adding a duotone filter on the Global Styles\" class=\"wp-image-16358595\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/08/image-2-1024x560.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/08/image-2-300x164.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/08/image-2-768x420.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/08/image-2-1536x840.png 1536w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/08/image-2-2048x1121.png 2048w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Reset options</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>While using the filter, you also have the option to revert whatever you want \u2014 this allow you to try and revert to experiement the image in different ways. To do so, click the <strong>Filters options</strong> button and select <strong>Reset all</strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"558\" src=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/08/image-1-1024x558.png\" alt=\"Example of clicking on &quot;Reset all&quot; for a duotone filter\" class=\"wp-image-16358591\" srcset=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/08/image-1-1024x558.png 1024w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/08/image-1-300x163.png 300w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/08/image-1-768x418.png 768w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/08/image-1-1536x837.png 1536w, https://wordpress.org/documentation/files/2023/08/image-1-2048x1116.png 2048w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Supported blocks</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The filter is currently avaliable in the following blocks:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/image-block/\">Image Block</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/cover-block/\">Cover Block</a></li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/documentation/article/gallery-block/\">Gallery Block</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<div style=\"height:69px\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-spacer\"></div>\n\n\n\n<div id=\"changelog\" class=\"wp-block-group changelog has-background is-layout-flow wp-block-group-is-layout-flow\" style=\"background-color:#dce5ec\">\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading has-medium-font-size\">Changelog</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Updated 2023-08-24\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Moved the category to Block Editor</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Edited some text</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Created 2023-08-09</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n",
